          <div class="feature" id="feature-1">
            <h2>
              Automatic sorting
            </h2>
            <p>
              Gmail uses a variety of signals to identify important email, including which messages
              you open and which you reply to.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature" id="feature-2">
            <h2>
              Sections keep you organized
            </h2>
            <p>
              Incoming email gets separated into sections: important and unread, starred, and
              everything else. Don’t like these? Customize them.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature feature-last" id="feature-3">
            <h2>
              Predictions improve over time
            </h2>
            <p>
              Over time, Priority Inbox gets better at predicting what’s important to you. You can
              help train it using the <img alt="Gmail priority inbox buttons" src=
              "/mail/help/images/priority-inbox-buttons.gif"> buttons.
            </p>
